Part 4 — Architectural separation (do not fold integrity into Stage 3)
Pipeline integrity and source data health checks must remain as separate stages (Stages 4 and 5). Stage 3 references the integrity work in its copy but does not display the integrity details — those remain in their dedicated stages. This preserves auditability and the meaningful separation between process-level integrity and content-level data health.
Document this decision by adding a new section to STAGE_PAGE_DESIGN_SPEC.md titled "Stage architecture: separation of concerns" with the following content:
"Stage 3 (Publish) delivers the dataset and articulates its role as the trusted analytics foundation. Stage 4 (Pipeline Integrity) and Stage 5 (Source Data Health) provide the quality evidence that supports the dataset's certification. These three stages are intentionally separate because they answer different questions, are owned by different roles, and serve different audit purposes. Stage 3 references Stages 4 and 5 in its copy but never absorbs their content."
